ce:section.ce:para:
A 26,650 LIB (specifications provided in Fig. 2


                     ) was fully charged in an experiment as shown in Fig. 5
                     , using the constant-current constant-voltage (CCCV) protocol with a LIB charger (UP300A). The first phase was constant current, and then the UP300A transitioned to the constant voltage phase. Fig. 5 shows a system for monitoring the LIB 's temperature during the charging process. Thermocouples are attached to the LIB to measure its temperature, and these sensors send the data to a data logger, which records the temperature in real-time and potentially displays it. The LIB is connected to a charger, ensuring that the LIB remains within a safe temperature range throughout the charging process.
